EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to an electric vehicle advisory committee.
EventItemMatterName: Electric vehicle charging stand pilot program.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to regulating sidewalk electric vehicle charging stands as revocable consents.
EventItemMatterName: Regulating sidewalk electric vehicle charging stands as revocable consents.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring that all hotels in the city of New York provide their housekeeping staff with silent alarms for their protection.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring that all hotels in NYC provide their housekeeping staff with silent alarms for their protection.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to enact and the Governor to sign A. 7707A-2011 and S. 6431-2011, which would prohibit the possession, sale, offer for sale, trade, or distribution of shark fins.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibit the possession, sale, offer for sale, trade, or distribution of shark fins. (A.7707A/ S.6431)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to allowing owners of landmarked properties to use the same or similar materials in maintenance of their property .
EventItemMatterName: Allowing owners of landmarked properties to use the same or similar materials in maintenance of their property .

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to additional guidelines and procedures to the designation process for a landmark, interior landmark, scenic landmark and historic district.
EventItemMatterName: Additional guidelines and procedures to the designation process for a landmark, interior landmark, scenic landmark and historic district.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to a transfer of jurisdiction over Hart Island from the department of corrections to the department of parks and recreation.
EventItemMatterName: Transfer of jurisdiction over Hart Island from the department of corrections to the department of parks and recreation.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the police department to report incidents of assaults on municipal employees on the department’s website.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the police department to report incidents of assaults on municipal employees on the department’s website.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to introduce, and the Governor to sign, legislation which would amend the Real Property Tax Law to allow owners of not-for-profit organizations to submit documentation other than the application prepared and mailed to such owner by the Department of Finance to prove such organizations are entitled to a property tax exemption.
EventItemMatterName: Allow owners of not-for-profit organizations to submit documentation other than the application prepared and mailed to such owner by the Department of Finance to prove such organizations are entitled to a property tax exemption.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Mental Health, Mental Retardation, Alcoholism, Drug Abuse and Disability Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to enact and the President to sign S.1872/H.R.3423, the Achieving a Better Life Experience (ABLE) Act of 2011, which amends the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to provide for the tax treatment of ABLE accounts established under State programs for the care of family members with disabilities, and for other purposes.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to enact and the President to sign S.1872/H.R.3423, the Achieving a Better Life Experience (ABLE) Act of 2011.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the landmarks preservation commission to create a timeline for the designation process.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the landmarks preservation commission to create a timeline for the designation process.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the landmarks preservation commission to allow denied requests for evaluation to be nominated to the landmarks preservation commission entire body for a vote.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the landmarks preservation commission to allow denied requests for evaluation to be nominated to the landmarks preservation commission entire body for a vote.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Parks and Recreation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to waiving parks permit fees for schools and child day care centers and providing an online system for school permit applications.
EventItemMatterName: Waiving parks permit fees for schools and child day care centers and providing an online system for school permit applications.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education’s Office of School Food to increase the health of food options in school lunches and breakfasts by implementing the recommendations of the Brooklyn Food Coalition’s “Roadmap for Healthy, Sustainable School Food.”
EventItemMatterName: Implementing the recommendations of the Brooklyn Food Coalition’s “Roadmap for Healthy, Sustainable School Food.”

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to licensing car washes.
EventItemMatterName: Licensing car washes.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign A.9664/S.6493, legislation to ease the burden on licensed home care service agencies, certified home health agencies and consumer directed personal assisted programs.
EventItemMatterName: Ease the burden on licensed home care service agencies, certified home health agencies and consumer directed personal assisted programs. (A.9664/S.6493)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the State Senate and State Assembly to pass and the Governor to sign S.4098/A.6275, which would provide that persons living with clinical/symptomatic HIV or AIDS who are receiving shelter assistance or an emergency shelter allowance shall not be required to pay more than 30% of household income towards shelter costs, including rent and utilities.
EventItemMatterName: Provide that persons living with clinical/symptomatic HIV or AIDS who are receiving shelter assistance or an emergency shelter allowance shall not be required to pay more than 30% of household income towards shelter costs, including rent and utilities. (S

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the reuse or recycling of discarded carpeting from commercial units or buildings.
EventItemMatterName: Reuse or recycling of discarded carpeting from commercial units or buildings.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign legislation that would require the New York Public Library, the Brooklyn Public Library, and the Queens Borough Public Library to install surveillance cameras in all designated children’s sections.
EventItemMatterName: Require the NY Public Library, the Brooklyn Public Library, and the Queens Borough Public Library to install surveillance cameras in all designated children’s sections.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Assembly to pass and the Governor to sign into law S.5260-C/A.7251-C, which would amend the Penal Law to establish the offense of fraudulent prescription, dispensing and procurement of non-controlled substance prescription medications and devices, and the offense of unlawful possession of non-controlled substance prescription medications and devices.
EventItemMatterName: Establish the offense of fraudulent prescription, dispensing and procurement of non-controlled substance prescription medications and devices. (S.5260-C/A.7251-C)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of S.2000, which would amend the Criminal Procedure Law in order to limit plea bargains for individuals charged with a sex offense felony or a specified felony offense, and calling on the Assembly to pass a companion bill, and on the Governor to sign such legislation.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the Criminal Procedure Law in order to limit plea bargains for individuals charged with a sex offense felony or a specified felony offense, and calling on the Assembly to pass a companion bill, and on the Governor to sign such legislation. (S.2000)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of A.9148/S.6413, which would raise the state minimum wage, and calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign this legislation.
EventItemMatterName: Raise the state minimum wage. (A.9148/S.6413)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature and the Governor to amend the New York State Penal Law by increasing penalties for the unintentional discharge of a firearm resulting in an injury to an individual.
EventItemMatterName: Increasing penalties for the unintentional discharge of a firearm resulting in an injury to an individual.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Senate and the New York State Assembly to pass and the Governor to sign A.4672B and S.641B, which would enhance the criminal penalties for assaulting an employee of a local social services district or juvenile detention agency while such employee is in the performance of his or her duties.
EventItemMatterName: Enhance the criminal penalties for assaulting an employee of a local social services district or juvenile detention agency while such employee is in the performance of his or her duties. (A.4672B and S.641B)
